Class EdgeListDataSet

  • java.lang.Object
    • bigobject.LiveDistributedObject<java.lang.Object,java.io.Serializable>

            • biggrph.dataset.EdgeListDataSet

  • public class EdgeListDataSet
extends BigGrphDataSet
    An EdgeListDataSet represent a graph data stored in a edge list file, that is a set of edges as a couple of two long integers. The first number is the source and the second is the destination of the edge.
    Graph Datasets are created either by specifying a name as a String object, or by specifying a file with a RegularFile object. A string argument to the constructor is supposed to be the name of a file containing the graph data and located inside the application dataset directory. A RegularFile argument is supposed to specify the full path of the graph data file, without any interaction with the dataset directory.
